Male genitalia (
Fig. 32
). Coremata developed, located at intersegmental membrane between seventh segment and eighth segment. Uncus bullet-like, wide at base, slightly narrowed at apex, with long setae laterally. Gnathos elongate triangular, gradually narrowed from base to apex, apex downcurved in lateral view. Tegumen with height approximately twice length of uncus, with a triangular peniculi at anterior 1/3 laterally. Valva almost uniformly wide to obtusely rounded apex; costa produced rectangularly, humped; inner process hooked; cucullus short, subtriangular, straight on dorsal margin, slightly produced dorsoapically, rounded at apex; sacculus approximately 3/4 length of valva, narrowly banded, rounded at apex, ventral margin slightly concave at basal 2/5, with long setae. Vinculum narrowly banded. Juxta inverted sub-triangular, broadly obtuse on posterior margin, pointed anteriorly; anellar lobes clubbed, with long setae. Aedeagus approximately 1.5 times length of valva, broad at base, slightly tapered to apex, with a widely banded sclerite at base; distal process clubbed, rounded at apex, 1/4 length of aedeagus; cornutus absent.

Female genitalia (
Fig. 55
). Papillae anales longer than wide, with short setae. Intersegmental membrane between papillae anales and eighth abdominal segment approximately three times length of papillae anales. Apophyses posteriores approximately 1.5 times length of apophyses anteriores. Eighth segment straight on posterior margin, with long setae; eighth tergite rectangular; eighth sternite concave in broad V-shape anteromedially. Antrum cupshaped, with dense microspines on inner surface, posteriorly with an inverted conical plate 3/5 length of antrum, concave anteriorly. Ductus bursae almost uniformly wide, approximately 7/10 length of corpus bursae. Corpus bursae sub-oval; two signa located at middle of corpus bursae, edged with microspines, larger one furcate on one end, approximately twice length of smaller one. Appendix bursae posterior to corpus bursae, elongate tubular, longer than corpus bursae, with dense 50 large denticles; bulla rounded, located at middle; ductus seminalis slender, with numerous granules.
